anvil.api.Command

Class CommandType

  • java.lang.Object
    • anvil.api.Command.CommandType

  • public class CommandType
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a type of wrapper command recognized by Anvil.

    Wrapper commands are treated separately from in-game commands, as they don't have any auto-fills and use a separate delimiter. Fiddling with the CommandPermissions changes who can call what commands.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Garrett Stonis
    See Also:
    CommandPermissions, CommandExecutionData, Command

    • Constructor Detail

      • CommandType

        public CommandType(java.lang.String name,
                   java.lang.String[] arguments,
                   CommandPermissions permissions,
                   CommandExecutionData data)
        Constructs a CommandType object with the given name and arguments.

        The name is checked with String.equals(Object) while each argument is checked with regex patterns.

        Parameters:
        name - String object containing the name of the CommandType. Multiple CommandTypes can have the same name. Cannot be null or contain '33'/'32'.
        arguments - Array of String objects, each containing a regex pattern representing an argument.
        permissions - The permission level of the CommandType. This baselines who can run the command.
        data - Execution data of the CommandType; what happens when the Command is called.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - When the name or arguments are illegal.
        See Also:
        CommandExecutionData, CommandPermissions

      • CommandType

        public CommandType(java.lang.String commandTypeString,
                   CommandPermissions permissions,
                   CommandExecutionData data)
        Constructs a CommandType object with the given commandTypeString. The commandTypeString is interpreted exactly how it would appear in the toString() method.

        The name is checked with String.equals(Object) while each argument is checked with regex patterns.

        Parameters:
        commandTypeString - String object containing the CommandType.
        permissions - The permission level of the CommandType. This baselines who can run the command.
        data - Execution data of the CommandType; what happens when the Command is called.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - When the given commandTypeString is not properly formatted.
        See Also:
        CommandPermissions, CommandExecutionData

    • Method Detail

      • passes

        public boolean passes(java.lang.String commandString)
        Tells whether or not a given String object passes the constraints provided by the CommandType.

        The name of the CommandType must pass the String.equals(Object) check, while each argument needs to pass a regex pattern. (Watch out for PatternSyntaxExceptions, they might trip up some arguments).

        Refer to here for more information on regex Patterns.

        Parameters:
        commandString - String object to be tested. Must include the 33 at the beginning.
        Returns:
        Whether or not the given String object passes the CommandType constraints.

      • addCommandTypeToKnowns

        public static boolean addCommandTypeToKnowns(CommandType newCommandType)
        Adds a given CommandType to the wrapper's list of known CommandTypes.

        Each added CommandType object should be mutually exclusive in terms of the passes() method. This means that no 2 CommandType objects should allow the same Command or String pass. Failing to do this will cause inconsistencies in CommandType detection.

        If newCommandType has the same name as any other known CommandType object, they are considered to be in the same group.

        Parameters:
        newCommandType - CommandType object to add.
        Returns:
        Whether or not the add was successful.

      • getKnownCommandTypeGroup

        public static CommandType[] getKnownCommandTypeGroup(java.lang.String name)
        Gets an array of CommandType objects in the known CommandTypes of the wrapper by a given name. These were added using the addCommandTypeToKnowns(CommandType) method.
        Parameters:
        name - String object containing the name of the desired CommandType group. All members of the group will have a name that passes the String.equals check with the given name.
        Returns:
        Array containing all known CommandType objects with the given name. Null if there are none.

        Returns:
